/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:46:  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay mHighlightOverlay;
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:50:Use `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::GetOverlayMode` when local logic needs to branch on the current mode. Use `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::SetOverlayMode` to switch directly between `Dali::Ui::OverlayHighlightMode::AUTO` and `Dali::Ui::OverlayHighlightMode::MANUAL`.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:53:void ConfigureHighlightMode(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay, bool customBounds)
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:62:Use `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::UpdateOverlay` when the accessibility focus target changes and the overlay should track the active highlight target. The method takes the active highlight object as `Dali::Actor&`; application code should still treat the dali-ui `Dali::Ui::View` tree as the app-facing model and keep direct actor handling inside the accessibility bridge or controller that receives the active highlight handle.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:78:  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay mHighlightOverlay;
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:82:In automatic mode, `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay` calculates the overlay rectangle from the active highlight target during `UpdateOverlay`. Keep `UpdateOverlay` calls tied to actual focus or highlight changes rather than calling it as a general frame update.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:85:void RefreshAutomaticOverlay(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay,
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:99:Use `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::SetCustomHighlight` when the app or accessibility layer already knows the exact overlay rectangle. The position and size are passed as `Dali::Vector2` values. Calling `SetCustomHighlight` also switches the overlay to `Dali::Ui::OverlayHighlightMode::MANUAL`.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:105:void ShowManualHighlight(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay,
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:119:void MoveManualHighlight(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay,
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:135:Use `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::HideOverlay` when the current accessibility highlight should no longer be visible, for example when focus leaves the relevant content area.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:138:void ClearVisibleHighlight(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay)
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:144:Use `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::ResetCustomHighlight` to clear the manual rectangle and return the overlay to automatic mode.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:147:void ReturnToAutomaticHighlight(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay,
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/generated/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md:159:A common flow is to hide the current overlay, reset any custom rectangle, and then let the next focus update call `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::UpdateOverlay` in automatic mode.
